'''Elizabeth Anne McCauley''' is [[David Hunter McAlpin]] Professor of the [[History of Photography]] and [[Modern Art]] at [[Princeton University]].
She graduated from [[ Yale University]]. Her work deals with 19th- and early-20th-century [[visual culture]], particularly the history of photography.<ref>{{cite web|title=Elizabeth Anne McCauley|url=https://artandarchaeology.princeton.edu/people/faculty/elizabeth-anne-mccauley|website=artandarchaeology.princeton.edu|publisher=Princeton University|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>
==Works== * ''[[A. A. E. Disdéri]] and the Carte de Visite Portrait Photograph'' ([[Yale University Press]], 1985) {{OCLC|228668690}} * ''Industrial Madness: Commercial Photography in Paris, 1848-1871'' (Yale University Press, 1994) {{ISBN|9780300038545}}, {{OCLC|28585299}} * ''The Museum and the Photograph'' with Mark Haworth-Booth (Sterling and Francine Clark Art Institute, 1998) {{ISBN|9780931102400}}, {{OCLC|37935241}} * ''Gondola Days: [[Isabella Stewart Gardner]] and the [[Palazzo Barbaro]] Circle'' with Alan Chong, Rosella Mamella Zorzi, and Richard Lingner ([[Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum]], 2004) {{ISBN|9780914660217}}, {{OCLC|938200301}} * ''The Steerage and [[Alfred Stieglitz]]'' with [[Jason Francisco]] ([[University of California Press]], 2012) {{OCLC|755640723}}
